The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Awards for future leaders

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Dec. 7: Infocom 2006 has instituted the Infocom Future Leadership Awards to nurture and encourage the leaders of tomorrow.

 We plan to continue with these awards over the years, said D.D. Purkayastha, executive director and COO of ABP Pvt Ltd and organising secretary of Infocom 2006. Six participants, three each from India and abroad, received the awards from the President during the inaugural ceremony of Infocom 2006, he added.

 A panel of judges had to choose the winners from more than 500 participants from over 60 B-schools worldwide. Each of them had to write a paper on innovate to differentiate. The work of Praveen Krishnan of IIM-Bangalore was adjudged the best and he received a cash prize of $1000. 




